main event: Three red and white circular objects were observed in Elkhorn, Wisconsin on May 29, 1957.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 10 minutes,Observers initially thought the lights were from an aircraft until a white light appeared and the lights separated,The objects emitted a sound that was dimmer than the normal noise of aircraft,Two witnesses reported seeing the same object and thought it to be a flare,There were no reports of air traffic in the area at the time of the observation.
sighted object: three red and white circular objects
witness description: two unnamed observers in a car
